In a message dated 12/4/2002 5:57:44 AM Pacific Standard Time, 
collie(-at-)ifoundit.ca writes:
> How easy, or if even possible, is it putting a 71+ balljoint, disc brakes 
> front beam in a split? I don't have my bay windows at home to judge against 
> my split...

Hi Collie,
If you have a 68/69 front beam you can install the disc brakes on that beam 
and fit it in your pre-1968 bus.  The problem is that will raise the front of 
the bus.  So you will either have to raise the rear (Not recommended without 
going to IRS!) or figure out how to lower the front.
Eric&Barb
